original: Bäckman, Frans Valdemar Alexius, arkitekt SAR, Göteborg, f. 18/8/91 i Gbg av köpm. Sven B. o. Anna Bäckman. — CTH 21. Studiresa t. Tyski. 21. Anst. i Byggn:firman F. O. Peterson & Söner i Gbg sed. 40 samt egen arkit iverksamh. Led. av SAR, Tekn. samif. i Gbg o. Byggn:tekn. fören. där. Hobbies: teckning o. målning.
translated: Bäckman, Frans Valdemar Alexius, architect SAR, Gothenburg, born August 18, 1891 in Gothenburg to merchant Sven B. and Anna Bäckman. Graduated from Chalmers University of Technology in 1921 and took a study trip to Germany. Employed at the construction firm F.O. Peterson & Sons in Gothenburg since 1940 and also worked as a self-employed architect. Member of SAR, the Technical Society in Gothenburg, and the Building Technology Association there. Hobbies include drawing and painting.
